SIMPLE: owing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Owing
<hw>Ow`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <ety>[Used in a
passive sense for <ets>owed</ets> (AS. <ets>⟦amac⟧gen</ets>. See
<er>Own</er>).]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Had or held under obligation of
paying; due.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is more <qex>owing</qex> her than is paid.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Had or experienced as a consequence, result, issue,
etc.; ascribable; -- with <xex>to</xex>; <as>as, misfortunes are often
<ex>owing</ex> to vices; his failure was <ex>owing</ex> to
speculations.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Owl</ent>⟦br⟧
